5.5 MV TN11 Tandem Accelerator of
N.C.S.R. 'Demokritos', Athens, Greece
Two thin targets were used, isotopically enriched LiF
target, 6Li enrichment 94% and a CaF(2).
The LiF target used, consisted of a thin carbon foil of
52+-2 mug/cm**2 thickness, a LiF layer of
(1017+-40)*E+15 at/cm**2, that was evaporated onto the
carbon foil and additionally of a thin gold layer of
(61+- 4)*E+15 at/cm**2, that was evaporated onto the
LiF layer. The CaF(2) target was produced in the same
way as the LiF one. More specifically, a CaF2 layer of
(875+- 35)*E+15 at/cm**2 was evaporated onto a similar
carbon foil and then additionally a similar gold layer
was evaporated onto the CaF(2) layer.
